We reached here close to 8pm.

I could easily find a parking lot. Not much of a crowd and I guess it could be attributed to the time perhaps?

As compared to other pasar malams that I've been to, the food offerings here felt a little slim to me. However, you can definitely buy something to tickle your tastebuds for sure.

The kerepok lekor stall is worth buying from. RM 1 for 4 pieces. I bought the sambal lekor and the texture was good.

I saw a stall Ucu Kway Teow Kerang stall. It looks good and you can consider buying from them.

What I did buy was from an unassuming western stall. He was selling buttermilk spaghetti and carbonara meatball pasta. The buttermilk spaghetti was nice except that it's cold. Even though it's cold, it's still . It would be a good idea for you to heat it up at home and enjoy it when it's warm.

When I went past the pasar malam at 930pm, it was closed. So I guess they cease operations quite fast.
